<h1>Veggie Omelet</h1>
<h2>Oyinkansola Famulegun</h2>
<p>One would make a veggie omelete in order to kickstart a pleasant day. Omeletes are indeed the breakfast of champions.</p>
<h3>Ingredients</h3>
<ul>
<li>4 eggs</li>
<li>2 tablespoons milk</li> 
<li>2 tablespoons butter</li> 
<li>1 small chopped onion</li> 
<li>2 ounces shredded cheese</li> 
<li>1 chopped green pepper</li> 
<li>1 chopped tomato</li> 
<li>Salt andÂ pepper to taste </li>
</ul>
<h3>What to do</h4>
<ol>
<li>Melt butter in skillet and add chopped vegetables</li>
<li>While vegetables are cooking, beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper</li>
<li>Add eggs to skillet, flip egg once bubbles begin to form</li>
<li>Sprinkle cheese on eggs</li>
<li>Fold eggs and remove from heat</li>
</ol>
